The paper discusses the use of neural networks to represent symbolic structures, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the ability of neural networks to achieve combinatorial generalization, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the need for specific mechanisms or training routines to support symbolic processing, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
